# ==============================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================
# 
# IMPORTANT: This .gitignore is designed to prevent
# accidental commits of sensitive data. Always:
# 
# 1. Review files before committing
# 2. Use 'git status' to check what will be committed
# 3. Never force-add ignored files with 'git add -f'
# 4. Regularly audit your repository for sensitive data
# 5. Use environment variables for all secrets
# 
# If you accidentally commit sensitive data:
# 1. Remove it immediately
# 2. Change all exposed credentials
# 3. Consider using git-filter-branch or BFG Repo-Cleaner
# 4. Force push the cleaned history (if safe to do so)
# 
